				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \left\{ {\begin{array}{*{20}c} {\frac{{{\text{d}}S}}{{{\text{d}}t}} = - \frac{ I S}{N}} \\ {\frac{{{\text{d}}I}}{{{\text{d}}t}} = \frac{ I S}{N} - I} \\ {\frac{dR}{dt} = I} \\ \end{array} } \right. $$\end{document}dSdt=-ISNdIdt=ISN-IdRdt=Iwhere S is the stock of susceptible population, I is the stock of infected, R is the stock of removed population (either by death or recovery), and N is the sum of these three parameters.

This system is nonlinear. However, it is possible to derive its analytic solution in an implicit form. Other numerical tools include such Monte Carlo methods as the Gillespie algorithm. Firstly, note that from \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
